5:
So you couldn't find a recipient for
all of these items just by listening to
their voices, huh?
8:
Not for all of them. Only the ones on
this table.
14:
Gosh... I'm ashamed to say this, but
we don't exactly have a log of ALL
adventurer equipment...
18:
It'd be crazy if you did. Anyway, let's
take the ones we managed to
identify to their new owners.
21:
This one's bound for... the
orphanage?
25:
Yes. It's to be delivered to a child
that's staying there.
26:
It was his father's, but he... Well, you
know.
29: Damn. It's a tough world out there.
33:
Yes. This item wants to go there. To
the orphanage.
36:
I'll go deliver it. Please continue
searching for the owners. Of the
other items.
40: Will do! Have a safe trip, you two!
49:
Are you on the clock right now? 
Do you have time to pop on in for
some tea?
54:
I came to deliver items. And a
message.
59:
Oh, I see. Who should I call on today,
then?
64:
I have a whole set of tools for him.
This knife in particular is special. 
It contains the words of the previous
owner.
73:
Kerry, be a good boy and listen...
What Falsche is about to say is very
important for you to hear.
76:
Dad... is still alive! He's out there, and
he'll come back for me! Soon!
82:
It's okay. Not everyone can accept
what I have to tell them.
86:
Take this. I wrote it down. What his
father said.
89: If he isn't ready to hear it. Then...
91:
When the day comes. Please give
him this letter.
101:
It's hard on these kids... Staying here,
waiting for someone who won't ever
come back.
102:
I know it's not easy for you, either,
delivering these messages directly.
I'm sure you feel the pain too.
105:
But it's meaningful work. Please keep
it up.
109: Yes. I will. Until next time, then.
119: What? I didn't even say anything.
122:
I knew there would be times like this.
But I chose to keep going. To deliver
lost belongings.
125: You take pride in your work, huh?
129:
Yes. I do. It is very, very important to
me.
132:
Hmph. I guess I didn't need to worry
about you after all.
135:
If that's the case, then just keep
doing what you have been. You're
good at it.
Well, later.
150:
What's the matter? 
Your breathing is heavy.
159:
I understand. I can be of use here.
Allow me to help.
162:
Oh that's wonderful! You really are a
lifesaver! The Guild REALLY isn't cut
out for dealing with ghosts and
spirits and the like...
165: Yes. It's okay. Leave it all to me.
169:
Done! Thank you, Falsche! You're the
best.
